<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-09-25T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-09-25T13:00:00-05:00" n="197" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d197">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/9–2540:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss> to the Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Tuck</hi></persName>)</head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-25T14:00:00-04:00">September 25, 1940—2 p.m.</date></dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>223. Please ascertain from Colonel Christian and Captain Brereton
                                    whether any mention was made during the staff conversations at
                                    Asuncion of the possibility of Paraguay according aviation bases
                                    to the United States. If such mention was made please report
                                    fully by rush telegram.</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>